\label{sect:BC}

In order to check consistency of the supersymmetry projection rules on the exotic branes,
we apply them to a certain brane configuration.
In this paper we focus on the system in which a brane is ending on another brane.
A typical example is the system of an F-string ending on a D3-brane described in Figure \ref{fig:D3-F1}:

