Since the configuration in Figure \ref{fig:73-NS5} is derived from that in Figure \ref{fig:D3-F1} via the string ST$_{1234}$S-dualities, this should also preserve the 1/4-BPS condition.
This can be confirmed by using the supersymmetry projection rules on the IIB NS5-brane in (\ref{SPR-IIB-standard}) and the $7_3$-brane in (\ref{SPR-IIB-defect}).
The former is given as ${\epsilon} = \Gamma^{012348} {\epsilon}$ and the latter is ${\epsilon} = \Gamma^{01234567} {\epsilon}$.
